<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-803-640  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 803 640.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  August 27 1990 v4 n31 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CSC wins Treasury's System 90. (Computer Sciences Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Richardson, Jennifer.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer Sciences Corp (CSC) won the US Treasury Department's$48.8 million System 90 contract to supply computer hardware,software, system security, operations support services, task orderdevelopment and software development for Treasury's FinancialManagement Service (FMS).andP;  The 10-year contract will create afinancial management system intended to streamline accountingthroughout the federal government, including generating over 850million federal payments, overseeing $900 billion in collections,reconciling about 600 million checks and managing over 100revolving and trust funds.andP;  The system will replace the20-year-old batch-oriented tape processing system now used by FMSto process 450 million checks and 250 million electronic fundstransfers every year.andP;  The automated payments claims enhancementreconciliation (Pacer) system will be designed, tested andimplemented in the first phase of the contract; existingapplications will be migrated to System 90 in the second phase.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Sciences Corp. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    CSC.andO;Topic:     Government ContractsNational GovernmentGovernment AgencyFinancial ServicesIntegrated SystemsAccounting ServicesUnited States. Department of the Treasury. Financial ManagementService.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>